=== 成长 ===
Twitter公司经历了非常快速的发展。2007年时，平均每季度会产生400,000条消息，而到了2008年，这个数字已经增长至1亿。在2010年2月，Twitter用户平均每天会发送5000万条消息。<ref>{{Cite_news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/twitter/7297541/Twitter-users-send-50-million-tweets-per-day.html | work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] | title=Twitter Users Send 50 Million Tweets Per Day – Almost 600 Tweets Are Sent Every Second Through the Microblogging Site, According to Its Own Metrics | first=Claudine | last=Beaumont | date=2010-02-23 | accessdate=2011-02-07 | archive-date=2011-10-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012214434/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/twitter/7297541/Twitter-users-send-50-million-tweets-per-day.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>到2010年3月，Twitter官方一共记录了超过70,000款第三方应用程序。<ref>{{Cite_news|author=[[Staff_writer|Staff writer]]|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/digital/2010/03/twitter-registered-created|work=[[New_Statesman|New Statesman]]|title=Twitter Registers 1,500 Per Cent Growth in Users|date=2010-03-04|accessdate=2011-02-07|archive-date=2019-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503011352/https://www.newstatesman.com/digital/2010/03/twitter-registered-created|dead-url=no}}</ref>到2010年6月，根据Twitter提供的数据，平均每天会产生6500万条消息，也就是每秒750条消息。<ref>{{Cite_web|author=Garrett, Sean|title=Big Goals, Big Game, Big Records|url=http://blog.twitter.com/2010/06/big-goals-big-game-big-records.html|publisher=''Twitter Blog'' ([[blog|blog]] of Twitter)|accessdate=2011-02-07|date=2010-06-18|archive-date=2011-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110213095055/http://blog.twitter.com/2010/06/big-goals-big-game-big-records.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> Compete.com网站显示，Twitter早在2009年1月就已经从排名第22位的社交网络站点上升至第三位。<ref name="#1">{{Cite_web|author=Kazeniac, Andy|url=http://blog.compete.com/2009/02/09/facebook-myspace-twitter-social-network/|title=Social Networks: Facebook Takes Over Top Spot, Twitter Climbs|publisher=''Compete Pulse'' ([[blog|blog]] of [[compete.com|compete.com]])|date=2009-02-09|accessdate=2011-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721111825/http://blog.compete.com/2009/02/09/facebook-myspace-twitter-social-network/|archive-date=2011-07-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

